com.rshepard.atm

Class BankValidation

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.rshepard.atm.BankValidation

  • public class BankValidation
extends java.lang.Object
    Creates a virtual bank that stores account numbers, PINs, and a current account that is utilized by the Processor class for balance queries, validation, and transactions. This class also makes use of the singleton class Logger that logs transactions and generates receipts. PINs are in the form of String so that a number that starts with a zero can be used ex. "0001"

        public boolean verifyPin(Command pinCommand,
                         int accountNumber)
        This method is used to verify the pin number associated with the account number and returns a boolean. If PIN is verified it will log the action, initialize a receipt, and increment the transaction number
        Parameters:
        pinCommand - The PIN is wrapped in a command object
        accountNumber - The account number to be check against the PIN
        Returns:
        True if verified, False if not

      • verifyAccountNumber

        public boolean verifyAccountNumber(int accountNumber)
        Verifies the account number passed in against the account numbers that are loaded into this class, returns validation in the form of a boolean. Once verified it will load the account to be used in subsequent transactions. Will also log accesses on the passed account number and if process was verified.
        Parameters:
        accountNumber - Integer representing the account number to be verified.
        Returns:
        Returns True if verified and False if not.
